-- Spain Considers Raising University Tuition by 50%, El Mundo Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-04-19T17:52:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/spain-considers-raising-university-tuition-by-50-el-mundo-says.html
Spain ’s Education Minister Jose
Ignacio Wert has suggested the country’s regional governments
increase university tuition fees by as much as 50 percent,  El
Mundo  reported, without specifying how it obtained the
information.  Wert made the suggestion during a meeting today with
university representatives, El Mundo said. The goal of the
measure is for the regions won’t have to maintain the burden of
financing 85 percent of university costs, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
